         <abstract>
            <p>This paper shows how to solve a decision tree problem using integer linear programming. The sequential credit investigation/credit granting problem is solved as a specific application in which the analyst must decide how much credit information to purchase before making the decision to grant or deny a credit request. Other decision tree problems are also amenable to solution using integer programming. In addition, integer programming can be used to model a variety of more complex sequential decision problems.</p>
         </abstract>
